frameDefinitions: A Speaker conventionally uses a particular Term to refer to an Entity.
An Entity has existed for a length of time, the Age.
A member or members of a Class have just been  mentioned or are present in the discourse setting and now a different instance  (or group of instances) of the same class is referred to.
This frame presents a situation where there is a certain Number of instances of an Entity or a certain Number that quantifies a Unit.
An Entity is rated as unexpected for its context in terms of its magnitude.

An Item is picked out either by the order in which the members of a set would be encountered by an implicit cognizer, or by the order in which the members of a set participate in an event or state which serves as the Basis_of_order.
frameExamples: The pattern of conservation is similar to that found in C1_1, therefore we have <t>termed</t> this domain DC1 for divergent C1 domain.
This building is twenty thousand years <t>old</t>.
My husband left me for <t>another</t> woman -- and now wants to get back together again!
Only <t>two</t> senators voted in support of the president .
The <t>entire</t> apple was riddled with worms .
The <t>first</t> car from the left is a Magosix.
listRoleDefinitions: The type of <fen>Entity</fen> that is conventionally referred to by a <fen>Term</fen>.
The linguistic sign that is used for referring to a type of <fen>Entity</fen>.
The speaker or speech community that uses a <fen>Term</fen> to refer to a particular <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular age is under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is a function of the amount of time that the <fen>Entity</fen> has existed.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s age.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Age</fen> from the norm.
The Frame Element <fen>Expressor</fen> marks expressions that indicate a body part, gesture or other expression of the <fen>Entity</fen> that reflect its age.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is at a particular <fen>Age</fen>.
The general category of entity which has been referred to.
The instance of the <fen>Class</fen> that is added to the <fen>Initial_set</fen> of entities in the <fen>Class</fen>.
The previously mentioned group of entities of the <fen>Class</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Number</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Entity</fen> enumerated by the <fen>Number</fen>.

A <fen>Unit</fen> expresses some quantification of some property of an entity, event, or situation by providing a base value of the property combined with a <fen>Number</fen> expressing how the current value for the property relates to the <fen>Unit</fen>.
The item which is described in terms of its expectedness in the context.
The kind of entity that the <fen>Item</fen> belongs to.
A usually spatial reference point from which the implicit cognizer scans across the members of the <fen>Comparison_set</fen>.
A kind of event in which the members of the <fen>Comparison_set</fen>, including the <fen>Item</fen>, participate in a certain order.
The entity picked out by the implicit cognizer as occupying a certain place in the ordered <fen>Comparison_set</fen>.
A set of entites of which the <fen>Item</fen> is a member and which are ordered either by the <fen>Basis_of_order</fen> or by the order in which the implicit cognizer focuses attention on them.
